All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
Country
The first layer of the tree, each country contains its name, country code and a list of its associated providers.
DisplayPane
This class builds and fills the panel that shows the complete TrustedList and the results after filtering.
Filter
Abstract class for Filters.
FilterList
This class carries every filter and applies them all to the TrustedList
FilterPane
Abstract class that will be implemented in ProvideFilterPane, ServiceFilterPane and StatusFilterPane
FilterPanesAccordion
Class that contains all the filter panes.
FilterTreeCell<T>
A class containing a CheckBoxTreeCell implementation that supports the disabled property.
FilterTreeItem<T>
CheckBoxTreeItem subclass that implements the disabled property.
InfoPane
This class implements the information panel called upon click on an object in the Display Pane
JsonCountry
Class created to get the attributes of a country from a json file and create a new Country safely (with this system it's hard to modify items of the TrustedList, or add external objects).
JsonProvider
Class created to read the attributes of a Provider from a json file and create a new Provider safely (with this system it's hard * to modify items of the TrustedList, or add external objects).
JsonService
Class created to get the attributes of a Service from a json file and create a new Service safely (with this system it's hard to modify items of the TrustedList, or add external objects).
NavigationController
This class gets the built list from the TrustedListApiBuilder, gets the filtered list from the filters and acts as a mediator between front-end and back-end
Provider
Second layer of the tree, contains provider name, id, trustmark, a set of ServiceTypes, a set of associated services and the country which the provider belongs to.
ProviderFilter
The provider filter uses the provider's name and country to filter the list.
ProviderFilterPane
This class fills the ProviderFilterPane and inherits and implements methods from FilterPane.
Service
Last layer of the tree.
ServiceTypeFilter
The ServiceTypes filter browses the list and removes providers and services if they don't have the required serviceTypes, which are on the ServiceTypeFilter's whiteList
ServiceTypeFilterPane
This class extends the FilterPane and enable the filtering of the list by ServiceTypes, which are showed on a list of checkBoxes that the user can interact with
StatusFilter
The Status filter browses al the list and eliminates services that don't have the required statuses, which are saved on the filter's WhiteList
StatusFilterPane
This class extends the FilterPane and enable the filtering of the list by Statuses, which are showed on a list of checkBoxes that the user can interact with
TrustedEntityLabel
Creates Labels for each TrustedEntity carrying the name and a reference of it, which is useful to get information about the clicked item
TrustedList
It has been decided to organize the TrustedList in a treeView, so this class represents the root of the tree.
TrustedListApiBuilder
 
TrustedListBuilder
An interface that collects al the builder.
TrustedListEntity
Interface used to define each object of the TrustedList: Country, Provider and Service.
TrustedListJsonBuilder
This class builds the TrustedList using
TrustedServicesNavigatorApplication
